WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-IN

00:00:22.080 --> 00:00:25.240
Oh, God, this is like a detailed question.

00:03:56.280 --> 00:03:59.080
But my driver always tells me,
"Vijay sir had come here."

00:05:27.120 --> 00:05:30.360
Oh, God, this is like a detailed question.

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:55.040
So, I had this very...
like education is essential.

00:06:24.160 --> 00:06:28.240
Like, if somebody would come over,
I would...

00:06:38.480 --> 00:06:41.080
"Oh, she dances really well.
Dance for them."

00:07:15.640 --> 00:07:18.240
There's some time
between the two performances.

00:08:16.680 --> 00:08:19.320
But Kathak and all is, like,
a little classical, strict.

00:08:52.840 --> 00:08:54.200
And then, I was very studious.

00:09:31.480 --> 00:09:32.960
If there was a maths exam...

00:10:14.960 --> 00:10:16.640
"What's going on in life?" All of that.

00:10:31.800 --> 00:10:33.400
She would be like, "Solve this correctly."

00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:37.360
I got a good amount of spankings
from my mom.

00:10:37.440 --> 00:10:39.360
-Were you spanked?
-Yes, of course, I was.

00:10:39.440 --> 00:10:43.280
Like, running around the table,
then getting cornered in the balcony,

00:10:43.360 --> 00:10:45.880
and then getting a slap has happened.

00:10:47.720 --> 00:10:49.760
Properly. Slaps and all, properly.

00:11:25.520 --> 00:11:27.920
"What is the point
of studying so much?" You know?

00:12:17.640 --> 00:12:19.240
Because it was a thing,
like, "Why do you need to do this?"

00:12:31.800 --> 00:12:32.800
"Teach me how to dance."

00:12:32.880 --> 00:12:34.920
And I'm like, "It's too late now.
I can't teach you."

00:13:18.360 --> 00:13:20.600
And she was like,
"Engineering is quite tough."

00:14:00.240 --> 00:14:01.840
But okay,
maybe I'll make a software tomorrow.

00:14:16.440 --> 00:14:17.920
You know, I would lose my appetite.

00:14:18.000 --> 00:14:19.680
There would just be one glass of juice.

00:17:03.360 --> 00:17:04.640
Take some time, right? Two-three podcasts.

00:17:51.280 --> 00:17:53.600
It would increase
if I was off for ten days.

00:18:45.040 --> 00:18:47.240
Sometimes it's destiny, right?
It doesn't work out.

00:22:56.520 --> 00:22:57.760
"Yeah, okay.

00:22:57.840 --> 00:22:59.920
I'm very satisfied with my performance.

00:23:00.000 --> 00:23:02.600
It doesn't matter
if people don't like or validate it."

00:24:08.000 --> 00:24:10.160
Like, "You know, this is a big...

00:24:44.840 --> 00:24:46.560
"Okay, this doesn't work for me."

00:24:46.640 --> 00:24:49.120
Or, "I don't want to do this."

00:25:04.880 --> 00:25:07.000
I can make a choice
that I don't want to do this.

00:25:34.440 --> 00:25:36.840
My parents never made me feel
that there was no money.

00:26:12.640 --> 00:26:15.280
"Okay, just let me know how much..."

00:26:20.680 --> 00:26:22.920
-"Dad, how much do I have?"
-"Oh, that's all there is?" You know?

00:28:19.560 --> 00:28:21.680
I assimilate wherever I go.

00:34:14.480 --> 00:34:17.600
What are we talking about?
We came here for a different conversation.

00:34:18.960 --> 00:34:20.560
And where is this Mr. India personality?

00:34:51.280 --> 00:34:54.080
-You should have worn a Mr. India T-shirt.
-Why?

00:34:54.160 --> 00:34:57.320
Because we had Mr. India
sitting with us till now.

00:35:07.640 --> 00:35:08.640
Yeah.

00:35:09.840 --> 00:35:11.800
Fifteen minutes. From Chandigarh.

00:35:29.840 --> 00:35:31.320
This was right in front of me.

00:35:31.400 --> 00:35:33.120
He asks a lot of questions.

00:35:33.200 --> 00:35:34.440
I mean...

00:35:35.560 --> 00:35:37.520
Even, "Why did you eat this today?"

00:36:15.440 --> 00:36:16.840
We're discussing college.

00:36:16.920 --> 00:36:19.600
Then we shall get to transition
from college to...

00:36:36.680 --> 00:36:39.640
What somebody else has told you
that this had happened.

00:37:24.080 --> 00:37:26.840
I feel like sometimes, like...
it's like memory is full.

00:37:39.280 --> 00:37:40.680
Okay, great. Not a problem.

00:38:52.920 --> 00:38:54.680
Have you ever felt,
because of your height,

00:38:54.760 --> 00:38:55.800
"I should slouch a bit?"

00:38:55.880 --> 00:38:57.080
-No.
-It has happened to me.

00:38:57.160 --> 00:38:59.160
Slouching, no... Even today...

00:40:37.280 --> 00:40:40.000
You started with college, then...

00:40:40.080 --> 00:40:41.520
Which school were you from?

00:40:43.720 --> 00:40:45.000
-Which college?
-Yes, yes, yes? What?

00:40:45.080 --> 00:40:46.320
-What?
-Nothing. Which college?

00:42:43.520 --> 00:42:47.600
There have been many such instances.
In terms of roles also.

00:42:47.680 --> 00:42:50.600
You know that, "I have no idea
how I am going to pull this off. I..."

00:45:08.080 --> 00:45:10.760
Since childhood, it's been there
that I need to do well.

00:45:15.640 --> 00:45:19.160
"Why did you not answer
for these three marks out of 100?"

00:45:19.240 --> 00:45:20.600
That has happened, too.

00:45:20.680 --> 00:45:25.160
So that pressure of needing to do well
has always been there.

00:45:46.000 --> 00:45:47.320
"This is what you should do."

00:45:53.880 --> 00:45:55.840
When you were five years old...

00:46:31.880 --> 00:46:34.120
My sister also had to give tests.
Not that she didn't.

00:46:34.200 --> 00:46:35.800
But even if she didn't...

00:46:43.760 --> 00:46:46.040
I would eat while watching TV
and take two hours to finish.

00:46:46.120 --> 00:46:48.960
And she would be like,
"Go eat outside at the dining table."

00:46:49.040 --> 00:46:53.560
My sister would go out and put the roti
under the shelf and be like, "I'm done."

00:46:57.720 --> 00:46:59.160
Okay.

00:47:58.040 --> 00:47:59.600
What does that mean?

00:48:04.680 --> 00:48:05.880
No, this is not...

00:48:15.520 --> 00:48:16.560
For me, honestly...

00:48:31.040 --> 00:48:32.320
But he's saying that is...

00:48:33.040 --> 00:48:34.800
That's basic. That is necessary.

00:48:34.880 --> 00:48:37.680
Other than that,
you talk about the deeper things.

00:48:37.760 --> 00:48:39.080
That just leaves luck.

00:49:17.320 --> 00:49:19.360
So tell me what is the "different"?

00:49:19.440 --> 00:49:21.800
What is the "different"
in your "different type of hard work"?

00:49:54.040 --> 00:49:55.960
"Oh, she asks a lot of questions."

00:49:56.040 --> 00:49:57.600
Hmm. Me too.

00:49:59.040 --> 00:50:01.280
Yeah, everybody knows that.
It's so evident.

00:50:01.360 --> 00:50:02.880
"But she asks too many questions."

00:50:02.960 --> 00:50:04.080
"She has a lot of queries."

00:50:16.880 --> 00:50:18.320
"How else can I do this?"

00:50:18.400 --> 00:50:19.640
You know? "Should I do it this way?"

00:50:38.240 --> 00:50:39.880
"Oh, she asks too many questions."

00:50:39.960 --> 00:50:42.360
Firstly, if a woman is asking,
it's like, "She asks too many questions."

00:51:25.160 --> 00:51:27.560
Were you like this at school, too?
Asking questions?

00:51:27.640 --> 00:51:28.760
I was. If I didn't understand...

00:51:28.840 --> 00:51:30.800
I have a problem till I completely
understand something.

00:51:30.880 --> 00:51:32.160
-You will keep asking.
-I need to understand.

00:51:32.240 --> 00:51:34.480
Memorizing was just in certain subjects.

00:51:34.560 --> 00:51:37.720
The ones that didn't have
a lot to be understood, you know.

00:51:42.720 --> 00:51:44.880
Chemistry sometimes can be
a bit of memorizing.

00:52:40.440 --> 00:52:43.280
And in my head, I was like,
"I can do it for the sake of it."

00:52:58.920 --> 00:53:04.040
I firstly feel people, as in&lt;i&gt; 3 Idiots&lt;/i&gt;
they say, have "herd mentality."

00:55:58.920 --> 00:56:00.600
"This is not your cup of tea.

00:56:00.680 --> 00:56:03.080
This is a world for people
who are thick-skinned," and all.

00:58:30.880 --> 00:58:32.360
Yeah, so, on campus...

01:05:12.720 --> 01:05:15.040
I'm sure you're also curious
about what cricket is like.

01:05:15.120 --> 01:05:18.240
I mean, this hand-eye coordination,

01:05:18.320 --> 01:05:20.680
from what I understand,

01:05:20.760 --> 01:05:22.080
is a natural ability, not everyone...

01:05:22.160 --> 01:05:25.280
Like, some can see the slow ball,
some can see the fast one.

01:05:32.120 --> 01:05:33.960
There must be facilities for that now.

01:05:34.040 --> 01:05:36.400
But what's natural...

01:06:18.560 --> 01:06:20.320
If you don't have music in you, you don't.

01:06:20.400 --> 01:06:22.160
How much can you teach someone?

01:07:08.720 --> 01:07:09.720
It's a mental thing.

01:08:52.360 --> 01:08:54.600
Profitable is a separate thing, but...

01:08:59.640 --> 01:09:02.360
"We did 100 Cr. Wow, we did 100 Cr!"
Used to be a big deal.

01:09:02.440 --> 01:09:04.560
Now 100 Cr is also not a big deal.

01:09:15.080 --> 01:09:19.600
There was a phase where
the ones who adapted, progressed.

01:09:19.680 --> 01:09:20.840
Those who didn't were left behind.

01:09:20.920 --> 01:09:22.520
This phase that we had when...

01:09:25.520 --> 01:09:26.720
Everyone could see it. It was not working.

01:09:30.400 --> 01:09:33.280
After that, I think,
a lot of people had to change.

01:09:33.360 --> 01:09:35.600
And the ones who did, they survived.

01:09:47.040 --> 01:09:50.320
I guess my choice of words was wrong.
They are thriving, too.

01:09:57.960 --> 01:09:58.960
No at all.

01:10:00.720 --> 01:10:03.560
You talk about the stock market,
I'll defend it.

01:12:13.360 --> 01:12:15.840
Exactly. I think,
in a creative field... So...

01:12:16.960 --> 01:12:19.520
Spotify has given us
a lot of data on music.

01:12:21.360 --> 01:12:25.880
And a lot... All the big labels
have data analysts set up.

01:12:25.960 --> 01:12:29.400
Like, "This certain genre of music
can go this far.

01:12:29.480 --> 01:12:31.000
"This is when the drop should come in.

01:12:31.080 --> 01:12:33.040
"This is how long the build-up should be.

01:12:33.120 --> 01:12:34.920
"This is how long the song should be."

01:12:39.640 --> 01:12:41.200
I don't think it will be successful.

01:12:55.800 --> 01:12:58.720
The beauty that it is,
cannot be quantized.

01:12:59.880 --> 01:13:01.280
And that beauty...

01:13:02.680 --> 01:13:05.120
in film and music, in my opinion,

01:13:05.200 --> 01:13:06.920
-Is very beautiful.
-And Cricket.

01:13:43.840 --> 01:13:46.880
I'm anyway playing cricket
all days in the by-lanes.

01:13:53.480 --> 01:13:55.480
"Okay, great. Finally, I have come..."

01:15:25.280 --> 01:15:26.320
Then you pursue...

01:15:27.520 --> 01:15:29.120
-Yes.
-You...

01:15:33.840 --> 01:15:35.120
We just got to know this.

01:15:35.200 --> 01:15:37.480
This is a question
worth Rs. 3,20,000 on&lt;i&gt; KBC.&lt;/i&gt;

01:15:51.400 --> 01:15:52.600
Isn't it?

01:16:01.880 --> 01:16:03.040
I'm blushing.

01:16:04.320 --> 01:16:05.720
That's what I think.

01:16:14.640 --> 01:16:15.640
It is what it is now.

01:16:19.840 --> 01:16:22.160
"KL Rahul, the angry superstar",
whatever that may be.

01:16:24.160 --> 01:16:26.200
In the South,
your father's name is added first.

01:16:26.280 --> 01:16:27.280
-Yeah.
-Before your name.

01:16:32.280 --> 01:16:33.480
It's the name of the village...

01:16:34.240 --> 01:16:38.880
I haven't met a single person
from Mangalore whom I have not liked.

01:16:40.440 --> 01:16:41.600
We are both from there, too.

01:17:42.280 --> 01:17:43.480
I wait in line.

01:18:03.320 --> 01:18:05.120
So, if I get the urge to...

01:18:05.200 --> 01:18:07.360
You know what they say,
if it has come to mind, you should go.

01:18:07.440 --> 01:18:09.200
So, if it has crossed your mind,
you should go.

01:26:16.280 --> 01:26:18.920
It's a constant battle
that goes on, mentally.

01:27:14.160 --> 01:27:15.800
Not yesterday, the day before yesterday.

01:28:52.440 --> 01:28:54.400
I mean, it had never happened to me...

01:28:54.480 --> 01:28:56.000
A straight yorker.

01:28:57.960 --> 01:28:59.520
Okay, I was...

01:29:02.640 --> 01:29:05.400
I mean, small things,
nothing to get me expelled from school.

01:30:19.000 --> 01:30:21.920
First, they support you,
when you're the underdog.

01:30:48.400 --> 01:30:50.160
They enjoy it. "Did you see that?"

01:30:50.240 --> 01:30:51.840
"Did you see that? The movie flopped."

01:31:09.320 --> 01:31:10.600
-Negativity or some...
-You're being

01:31:10.680 --> 01:31:12.480
-really safe, aren't you?
-This is how it is.

01:31:22.440 --> 01:31:23.760
You are absolutely right.

01:31:32.760 --> 01:31:34.400
How can it affect me
if I don't even know about it?

01:31:44.600 --> 01:31:46.400
"Okay, this is where I find ignorance.

01:31:46.480 --> 01:31:47.880
"This is where I find bliss."

01:31:59.480 --> 01:32:00.640
There, I just feel like...

01:32:10.200 --> 01:32:11.720
But how long can you stay there?

01:32:11.800 --> 01:32:13.040
-You can't stay.
-You can't, right?

01:32:25.000 --> 01:32:26.320
Wow, you just flipped it.

01:33:37.360 --> 01:33:40.960
Not like, "I'm getting
social media validation, so, great."

01:33:55.960 --> 01:33:58.320
Basically, you cannot say "hard work".

01:34:01.880 --> 01:34:03.040
What else can I say?

01:34:03.120 --> 01:34:04.560
This answer is taken.

01:39:44.200 --> 01:39:45.720
Okay, we'll come back to Rahul.

01:39:47.480 --> 01:39:48.880
Yes?

01:39:59.960 --> 01:40:02.480
And let me tell you,
I have heard so many of your songs.

01:40:05.240 --> 01:40:07.240
This extra, for me...

01:40:07.320 --> 01:40:10.160
I don't want this complementary praise
alongside him.

01:40:21.040 --> 01:40:22.520
-So now...
-Favorite?

01:40:47.240 --> 01:40:48.240
I go to him just for wisdom.

01:41:05.960 --> 01:41:07.280
At that point...

01:41:08.600 --> 01:41:10.320
So, based on his movie,&lt;i&gt; Badshah...&lt;/i&gt;

01:41:20.480 --> 01:41:22.240
Before this, I used to rap in English,

01:41:22.320 --> 01:41:23.680
and my name used to be Cool Equal.

01:41:24.520 --> 01:41:25.840
-What was it?
-What was it?

01:41:33.240 --> 01:41:35.320
Once, when I was being introduced
on the stage,

01:41:35.400 --> 01:41:37.440
I was asked, "What should we call you?"
I said, "Cool Equal."

01:41:41.800 --> 01:41:44.360
And when I told my cousins...

01:41:44.440 --> 01:41:47.440
They are my mood...
They are my sounding boards.

01:41:48.160 --> 01:41:49.880
I do my audience-testing there.

01:42:03.560 --> 01:42:05.200
I mean, the amount I have...

01:42:07.880 --> 01:42:09.200
Yes, of course.

01:42:10.200 --> 01:42:12.640
Because, for me,
from what I have seen till now,

01:42:12.720 --> 01:42:15.800
if you are real, you become cool.

01:42:16.800 --> 01:42:18.560
No, dude. Who told you that?

01:42:19.280 --> 01:42:20.680
I mean, if you are a good person.

01:42:26.600 --> 01:42:28.040
I don't know if I am cool or not.

01:42:45.440 --> 01:42:47.640
Did you always have that cool factor?

01:42:47.720 --> 01:42:48.840
No, it developed...

01:43:00.720 --> 01:43:02.160
If you were there,

01:43:02.760 --> 01:43:03.880
what would you wish for?

01:43:04.840 --> 01:43:08.240
So that is a big... a huge driving factor.

01:43:10.640 --> 01:43:14.040
And sometimes, because of adrenaline,
you end up doing things

01:43:14.120 --> 01:43:15.560
which can turn out to be something good,

01:43:16.400 --> 01:43:18.200
or maybe something
that isn't right for that show.

01:43:23.400 --> 01:43:26.160
That is very... I think that is very...

01:43:46.200 --> 01:43:47.440
This...

01:43:48.280 --> 01:43:49.640
is very overwhelming.

01:43:55.680 --> 01:43:57.320
Sometimes I laugh too much.

01:43:57.400 --> 01:44:00.520
Sometimes I tear up
if someone sings really beautifully.

01:44:01.320 --> 01:44:04.160
A great scene, comedy... No, not comedy,

01:44:04.240 --> 01:44:06.360
but something else,
you watch it and you cry.

01:44:08.040 --> 01:44:11.240
And your emotions cannot be contained.

01:44:13.000 --> 01:44:14.280
Start from your childhood.

01:44:17.920 --> 01:44:19.360
What?

01:44:19.440 --> 01:44:21.400
What happened in life?
Where were you born?

01:44:21.480 --> 01:44:23.280
-Parents, siblings, everything.
-In Delhi, I was...

01:44:23.360 --> 01:44:25.080
-All questions in one, like that.
-Everything.

01:44:28.200 --> 01:44:30.200
My father was in a government job.

01:44:30.280 --> 01:44:32.200
-Mother was a teacher.
-What did he do for the government?

01:44:33.120 --> 01:44:34.880
In the Delhi Electricity Board.

01:44:53.440 --> 01:44:55.840
I would ask my father, like,
"Your colleague's sons have..."

01:44:59.760 --> 01:45:01.400
So, Mom was a teacher.

01:45:02.560 --> 01:45:05.080
She's retired. They are both retired.

01:45:05.160 --> 01:45:06.400
Everyone's mother here is a teacher.

01:45:18.480 --> 01:45:20.400
Then college.

01:45:23.080 --> 01:45:24.720
And then I went
to Punjab Engineering College

01:45:24.800 --> 01:45:26.880
from where I did my engineering, civil.

01:45:29.880 --> 01:45:31.480
What did you listen to?

01:45:37.440 --> 01:45:39.320
We had a lot of Punjabi music
playing at home.

01:45:39.400 --> 01:45:41.240
Gurdas Maan sir.

01:45:53.440 --> 01:45:57.600
So that's when I found Eminem, Tupac.

01:45:58.480 --> 01:46:00.480
He first introduced me
to the Backstreet Boys.

01:46:01.480 --> 01:46:04.240
They had a song that went...
&lt;i&gt;Get Down, Get Down.&lt;/i&gt;

01:46:05.000 --> 01:46:08.000
He gave it to me saying&lt;i&gt;,&lt;/i&gt;
"Listen to 'Quit Playing Games'."

01:46:08.080 --> 01:46:10.880
But I stopped at "Get Down"
because there's a small rap that comes in.

01:46:13.440 --> 01:46:14.720
Then, from there...

01:46:18.920 --> 01:46:20.880
There, I studied, did my engineering.

01:46:22.080 --> 01:46:23.360
And...

01:46:24.000 --> 01:46:26.040
There I got a taste of it.
I mean, Chandigarh...

01:46:27.840 --> 01:46:30.120
It's a beautiful place
when it comes to music, Punjab.

01:46:32.160 --> 01:46:36.360
Because they are directly
in touch with the West.

01:46:36.440 --> 01:46:37.720
It's a direct link.

01:46:37.800 --> 01:46:41.840
You don't go to Delhi from Chandigarh.
You go to Canada or USA.

01:46:41.920 --> 01:46:44.320
So, the amalgamation of cultures
that present there

01:46:44.400 --> 01:46:45.800
is very intimidating.

01:46:59.360 --> 01:47:01.680
If one person goes, everyone else follows.

01:47:16.280 --> 01:47:17.680
You have money there.

01:47:17.760 --> 01:47:19.800
They feel there are more opportunities.

01:47:19.880 --> 01:47:21.760
I mean, for me... Personally, I feel

01:47:21.840 --> 01:47:23.480
that if you want to do something,
you can do it anywhere.

01:47:23.560 --> 01:47:24.560
That's how I feel.

01:47:24.640 --> 01:47:27.640
You can do anything, anywhere,
whenever you want, if you wish to.

01:47:29.920 --> 01:47:33.720
So, if they see an example
of someone who has made a lot of money...

01:47:38.840 --> 01:47:40.840
It pulls you in.

01:48:04.560 --> 01:48:08.680
I know a bunch of people
who got inspired by this and failed.

01:48:10.400 --> 01:48:11.880
I mean, they feel that...

01:48:11.960 --> 01:48:14.880
Somehow, in some way,
they get this perception

01:48:14.960 --> 01:48:16.280
that doing this is very easy.

01:48:18.760 --> 01:48:20.720
When I started a business...

01:48:24.920 --> 01:48:27.040
I used to feel it was very easy.
A restaurant, for example.

01:48:28.320 --> 01:48:29.640
It's the worst thing.

01:48:31.880 --> 01:48:33.800
-It's difficult, not bad.
-Yeah, I mean...

01:49:03.520 --> 01:49:05.400
-People come in after seeing them.
-Yeah.

01:49:13.480 --> 01:49:14.480
And you...

01:49:16.960 --> 01:49:17.960
When you...

01:49:19.800 --> 01:49:20.840
Yeah.

01:49:28.080 --> 01:49:31.960
This... "Yeah, might as well do it.
It will work out."

01:49:55.240 --> 01:49:57.000
My podcast is successful today.

01:50:30.640 --> 01:50:32.200
And now let me find where to...

01:50:53.200 --> 01:50:54.840
-There's none anywhere here.
-It is here.

01:51:04.040 --> 01:51:05.520
I get affected by the evil eye, very fast.

01:51:05.600 --> 01:51:07.600
If I were to ask you to invest,

01:51:08.920 --> 01:51:09.920
let's say...

01:51:11.480 --> 01:51:13.760
two and a half to three crores,
blindly on a business...

01:51:14.920 --> 01:51:16.280
-Two and a half to three crores.
-Yeah.

01:52:56.320 --> 01:52:58.000
How much?

01:53:06.000 --> 01:53:07.880
Honestly, like...

01:54:19.480 --> 01:54:21.080
But I am not doing anything today.

01:54:48.680 --> 01:54:49.920
You are in a different zone now.

01:55:41.640 --> 01:55:42.640
It's difficult.

01:55:55.000 --> 01:55:56.080
And in India...

01:56:01.160 --> 01:56:02.480
Exactly. I have a question.

01:56:02.560 --> 01:56:04.120
Sorry, one...

01:56:07.160 --> 01:56:08.560
I had been waiting for this.

01:56:09.480 --> 01:56:11.760
These people are talking about
their childhood, I'm not interested.

01:56:18.200 --> 01:56:19.320
Not like Sabyasachi.

01:56:25.360 --> 01:56:26.520
Come on, bro.

01:56:27.160 --> 01:56:29.360
No, I mean, I was toying around.

01:56:43.080 --> 01:56:44.440
He has been doing it for 15 years.

01:56:58.960 --> 01:57:00.120
It's not possible here.

01:58:47.960 --> 01:58:49.760
Yeah, so that was...
I have one more question.

01:59:46.760 --> 01:59:48.160
"This won't work."

02:01:08.960 --> 02:01:10.320
Okay, you tell me.

02:01:20.560 --> 02:01:22.240
What else? Then music happened.

02:01:23.640 --> 02:01:24.920
Then my song became popular.

02:01:25.000 --> 02:01:27.680
But there must be a story behind it.

02:01:29.360 --> 02:01:32.120
Music happened, food worked out,
song worked out.

02:01:42.120 --> 02:01:43.520
As far as I can remember.

02:01:43.600 --> 02:01:45.120
I mean, for me, it would be like,

02:01:45.200 --> 02:01:46.720
if I ended up arguing
with someone in class,

02:01:46.800 --> 02:01:48.360
I couldn't come up with a comeback.

02:01:48.440 --> 02:01:50.040
Then I would think about it later,

02:01:50.120 --> 02:01:51.840
like, "I could have said this.
I could have said that."

02:02:06.160 --> 02:02:07.480
It started in school.

02:02:08.680 --> 02:02:09.680
And...

02:02:18.320 --> 02:02:21.120
Earlier, we didn't get the lyrics.
We didn't have the internet.

02:02:21.200 --> 02:02:23.440
So, if we heard a song,
we would write down the lyrics.

02:02:27.480 --> 02:02:28.480
That we would hear a song.

02:02:33.680 --> 02:02:36.600
So, we would write down the lyrics first
and then memorize them,

02:02:36.680 --> 02:02:38.240
perform it at school and become cool.

02:02:59.560 --> 02:03:00.720
That's how it started.

02:03:00.800 --> 02:03:02.600
So, when I went to Chandigarh...

02:03:02.680 --> 02:03:05.280
-From where did you go to Chandigarh?
-I went from Delhi to Chandigarh.

02:03:07.600 --> 02:03:11.480
I was admitted to Punjab Engineering
College, in civil engineering.

02:03:11.560 --> 02:03:12.680
And there...

02:03:13.960 --> 02:03:16.520
something beautiful was happening.

02:03:25.640 --> 02:03:30.040
And we were thinking,
"What kind of music are we making

02:03:30.120 --> 02:03:31.640
compared to the kind of music
that they were making?

02:03:31.720 --> 02:03:33.320
Why can't we make music like that?

02:03:42.840 --> 02:03:44.480
Like, even now,
I get goosebumps thinking about it.

02:03:44.560 --> 02:03:46.120
That, "Oh, my God."

02:03:46.200 --> 02:03:49.120
When I heard Rishi Rich's "Dance With You"
the first time, with Jay Sean,

02:03:49.200 --> 02:03:50.600
I didn't know he was one of our guys.

02:03:56.160 --> 02:03:57.480
So, I used to go
to our college's computer lab

02:03:57.560 --> 02:03:59.480
with the sole purpose
of downloading music.

02:03:59.560 --> 02:04:02.360
There were torrents,
we downloaded songs from Limewire.

02:04:04.400 --> 02:04:06.200
Passion kept increasing.

02:04:06.280 --> 02:04:10.480
I downloaded a mixing software,
made beats on it,

02:04:10.560 --> 02:04:12.160
and wrote.

02:04:12.240 --> 02:04:15.880
And once, I was playing basketball,
and while playing...

02:04:21.080 --> 02:04:23.800
Is there software available,
where I can...

02:04:29.840 --> 02:04:31.400
Where you get a lot of samples.

02:04:34.360 --> 02:04:37.160
I mean, you feel bad as a purist, but...

02:04:42.040 --> 02:04:45.240
Arrange three or four of them,
and a beat creates itself.

02:04:52.920 --> 02:04:55.160
Something that is your own.

02:04:59.840 --> 02:05:02.000
Nonsense. I mean, for me...

02:05:02.880 --> 02:05:04.000
I love "nonsense".

02:05:09.640 --> 02:05:12.920
And I keep saying it,
that in the coming years, I think...

02:05:19.040 --> 02:05:24.480
Maybe five years down the line
non-AI songs will be very expensive.

02:05:26.480 --> 02:05:29.600
That singer sang with his real voice.

02:05:48.960 --> 02:05:52.840
A lot, but technology has made it so easy
to become a recording artist.

02:05:55.520 --> 02:05:56.880
But live music has its place.

02:06:13.920 --> 02:06:16.040
It can be your voice.

02:06:16.120 --> 02:06:18.400
It can be a moment for them.

02:06:18.480 --> 02:06:20.400
It can be an audio-visual experience
for them.

02:06:23.280 --> 02:06:24.480
You're singing.

02:06:52.320 --> 02:06:53.360
It will grow immensely.

02:07:10.480 --> 02:07:11.920
Okay, and then?

02:07:17.440 --> 02:07:19.080
I met people.

02:07:50.200 --> 02:07:53.840
Back then, the music would reach you,
but the personalities would not.

02:07:56.120 --> 02:07:57.280
So, I met his manager.

02:07:58.240 --> 02:07:59.880
So he said he had heard one of my raps.

02:07:59.960 --> 02:08:01.200
He asked, "Did you do this?"
I said, "Yes."

02:08:01.280 --> 02:08:02.680
He asked, "Where are you from?

02:08:02.760 --> 02:08:05.000
"Are you from Canada or something?"
I said, "No, I'm from here."

02:08:07.240 --> 02:08:08.680
I didn't even have a passport.

02:08:09.840 --> 02:08:13.720
But he was like,
"This is a guy who makes music."

02:08:13.800 --> 02:08:16.880
I said, "I know him.
He makes insane music."

02:08:26.240 --> 02:08:28.840
At the time,
I was still doing my job. I...

02:08:32.200 --> 02:08:33.200
Where?

02:08:34.400 --> 02:08:35.960
I...

02:08:40.600 --> 02:08:42.600
How did you reach Himachal, bro?
From Chandigarh to Himachal?

02:08:42.680 --> 02:08:44.040
Bro, I...

02:08:48.160 --> 02:08:49.800
I took the CAT exam,
got a good percentile.

02:08:49.880 --> 02:08:51.120
But I got a government job.

02:08:53.720 --> 02:08:58.960
Then, I joined as an SDO in BBMB,
Bhakra Beas Management Board.

02:09:09.880 --> 02:09:11.280
They created electricity.

02:09:14.200 --> 02:09:15.560
I didn't have anything else then.

02:09:15.640 --> 02:09:17.480
So, I had to do a regular job.

02:09:17.560 --> 02:09:20.960
So I was shuffling between that job and...

02:09:24.200 --> 02:09:26.080
And that's when I knew that...

02:09:27.760 --> 02:09:30.760
"Bro, no one what doing what I did.

02:09:31.920 --> 02:09:34.240
I mean, I am killing it!"

02:09:35.600 --> 02:09:37.200
And at that time,
we didn't have rappers in India.

02:09:47.160 --> 02:09:49.400
And the confidence was such
that it was just us, nobody else existed.

02:09:49.480 --> 02:09:51.040
And that...

02:09:51.120 --> 02:09:53.000
And that borderline feels right,

02:09:53.080 --> 02:09:54.080
but borderline can be bad, too.

02:10:01.840 --> 02:10:03.320
Yes.

02:10:03.400 --> 02:10:07.880
-After that?
-After that, we parted ways in 2011.

02:10:07.960 --> 02:10:12.440
And in 2011, I found out
that I needed to learn how to make music.

02:10:26.280 --> 02:10:30.600
Which went bonkers in Delhi.

02:10:30.680 --> 02:10:32.280
People went insane, so...

02:10:54.040 --> 02:10:56.120
"This&lt;i&gt; Saturday Saturday &lt;/i&gt;is your song?"

02:10:57.520 --> 02:10:59.240
They said, "We want this song."

02:10:59.320 --> 02:11:01.240
I was like, "Take it."

02:11:01.320 --> 02:11:02.640
They said, "You come to Bombay."

02:11:03.160 --> 02:11:04.720
Now, take a look at my courage.

02:11:04.800 --> 02:11:06.880
I said, "If you want the song,
you come to Chandigarh."

02:11:14.160 --> 02:11:15.520
Then one after another...

02:11:15.600 --> 02:11:16.720
Did they come to Chandigarh

02:11:16.800 --> 02:11:18.560
-or did you go? They came?
-They came.

02:11:18.640 --> 02:11:20.120
-Yeah.
-Yeah, he came.

02:11:30.560 --> 02:11:32.960
And then it blew up, then...

02:11:58.400 --> 02:11:59.400
It was cool.

02:12:42.160 --> 02:12:43.440
Yesterday, I bought speakers.

02:12:44.280 --> 02:12:46.360
The ones where you can hear
my final output,

02:12:46.440 --> 02:12:48.760
I mix on those speakers, 12,000 rupees.

02:12:57.800 --> 02:12:59.440
Why do you want to do it?

02:13:00.400 --> 02:13:01.680
I want to become Badshah.

02:13:07.400 --> 02:13:08.720
It's very difficult.

02:13:10.920 --> 02:13:12.400
Same answer? "Very difficult"?

02:13:13.440 --> 02:13:15.080
No, I mean, why do you wanna be Badshah?

02:13:18.640 --> 02:13:21.840
If I tell you, stop you, scold you,

02:13:21.920 --> 02:13:24.640
that, "You don't do this."
And you go and do it again tomorrow...

02:13:33.600 --> 02:13:34.760
It will take time.

02:14:08.960 --> 02:14:10.320
You know what that depends on?

02:14:16.720 --> 02:14:19.600
You'll make music
when you have an audience,

02:14:19.680 --> 02:14:21.320
and still make music
even when you don't have one.

02:14:26.080 --> 02:14:27.600
Yes...

02:14:27.680 --> 02:14:29.120
Otherwise, it's easy to give up.

02:14:40.160 --> 02:14:42.120
I had only one plan in life.

02:14:42.200 --> 02:14:44.360
I never had a plan B.

02:15:00.360 --> 02:15:01.960
Even if that didn't happen,
I don't know, I mean...

02:15:19.280 --> 02:15:20.600
That, "I have to do this."

02:15:22.360 --> 02:15:23.560
That, "I have to do this."

02:15:27.600 --> 02:15:29.600
But for me...

02:15:46.440 --> 02:15:48.840
You start off very superficially.

02:15:48.920 --> 02:15:50.440
You don't even know where in the film...

02:15:50.520 --> 02:15:52.720
The mark is there.
You don't even know where the camera is.

02:15:59.120 --> 02:16:01.320
"It's only acting.
I can't even think of anything else."

02:16:02.520 --> 02:16:03.520
It was not that.

02:16:06.560 --> 02:16:08.520
"Where is the light coming from?
Where is the camera?"

02:20:53.040 --> 02:20:55.880
"Okay, so these roles, I cannot do it."

02:21:09.960 --> 02:21:11.920
Once you are married, you can't, you know.

02:22:16.280 --> 02:22:18.400
Gurdas Maan sir had said something to me.

02:22:21.040 --> 02:22:22.600
I didn't understand it then but I do now.

02:22:22.680 --> 02:22:24.400
That your work does not change.

02:22:25.560 --> 02:22:27.360
But people's perceptions change.

02:22:36.880 --> 02:22:40.200
That phenomenon,
how does it happen, why does it happen...

02:22:51.840 --> 02:22:54.960
I was still in school.
He has been singing for 22 years.

02:22:59.720 --> 02:23:02.600
I mean, you know, after a certain age,

02:23:02.680 --> 02:23:05.680
an artist or a creative develops an ego.

02:23:06.760 --> 02:23:09.200
Like, "No, it used to be like this.
Back in my day, it was like that.

02:23:09.280 --> 02:23:10.920
This is how it is."

02:23:40.640 --> 02:23:45.160
You don't have to
move along with the times.

02:23:45.240 --> 02:23:46.880
You have to move ahead of the times.

02:25:22.640 --> 02:25:23.640
What did you say?

02:25:24.960 --> 02:25:26.080
No, what was that word?

02:25:26.160 --> 02:25:28.200
-No, leave that.
-At least tell me the word.

02:25:42.600 --> 02:25:44.120
But first, you tell me the word.

02:25:48.680 --> 02:25:50.160
Okay, duopoly.

02:26:43.360 --> 02:26:44.360
He's off on a tangent.

02:27:01.240 --> 02:27:04.240
If he asked me, I would have taken
ten hours to answer him.

02:28:05.000 --> 02:28:06.520
Petty little things.

02:28:22.880 --> 02:28:24.040
Ask her as well.

02:28:24.960 --> 02:28:26.360
Oh, God, I have to answer now.

02:30:00.240 --> 02:30:01.320
What's up, guys?

02:30:06.000 --> 02:30:07.960
Tell me what's happening...

02:30:13.120 --> 02:30:14.400
Which girl are you dating today?

02:30:15.520 --> 02:30:16.720
-What do you mean "today"?
-Nowadays...

02:30:42.960 --> 02:30:45.520
In fact, recently, a lot of people...

02:30:45.600 --> 02:30:49.920
In general, I have distanced
a lot of people from my life.

02:30:52.760 --> 02:30:53.760
Even the slightest...

02:30:55.320 --> 02:30:58.520
Even the slightest answerability

02:30:58.600 --> 02:31:01.600
or even the slightest time-division...

02:35:03.840 --> 02:35:06.480
A 20-year-old wanna-be singer,
what would you tell them?

02:35:59.040 --> 02:36:01.680
Even if your story is exactly the same
as someone else.

02:36:02.720 --> 02:36:04.480
But if I say

02:36:04.560 --> 02:36:07.400
that I need to relieve myself,
in my own way.

02:36:43.800 --> 02:36:46.120
That's the stupidest thing.

02:37:26.840 --> 02:37:28.000
Bro?

02:37:28.080 --> 02:37:29.400
-Me?
-Yes.

02:37:42.160 --> 02:37:44.560
What else can be done
to leverage the brand?

02:38:14.960 --> 02:38:16.480
Sector as in?

02:38:16.560 --> 02:38:18.360
Sector, as in...

02:38:34.720 --> 02:38:35.960
Like, health, wellness.

02:40:10.400 --> 02:40:12.320
Sorry, I'm being greedy. Last question.

02:40:13.040 --> 02:40:14.320
How long does it take, normally...

02:40:15.920 --> 02:40:18.840
to know if it is a good business
or a bad one?

02:40:18.920 --> 02:40:20.840
-How long? A year?
-A year or two.

02:40:22.720 --> 02:40:24.160
One and two maybe...

02:40:53.280 --> 02:40:56.760
Like, a foreigner is coming in
and investing in Company X.

02:41:29.000 --> 02:41:31.000
Subtitles by Clockwork Captions

